What you need to know:

A report on the first nine months of this year by the Unclaimed Financial Assets Authority (Ufaa) says money surrendered by telcos stood at Sh1.76 billion up from 2018 full year release of Sh1.19 billion where Ufaa received Sh340.6 million a year earlier.Leaving of huge amounts of money in mobile wallets could have been informed by growing scrutiny and monitoring of transfer of large sums across mobile networks by State agencies fighting terrorism, money laundering and corruption.The Assets Recovery Authority, the Ethics and Anti-corruption Authority as well as the Directorate of Criminal Investigations and the Anti-banking Fraud Unit have been closing following traces of suspicious money transfers.